The paper primarily focuses on the application of game theory in wireless networks, specifically in the context of multiaccess edge computing (MEC). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of theoretical games, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of resources and balancing tradeoffs, which could fall under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of game models, which could fall under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
